# Keep the LLD README updated

Whenever a new design pattern is implemented (a new pattern package appears
under `src/main/java/com/lld/{creational,structural,behavioral}/`), or an
existing one changes meaningfully, update `README.md` in the same turn.

## What to update in `README.md`

Under the **## Patterns implemented** section, add or edit the pattern's entry
following the existing format. Include:

- A `### <Pattern> (<category>) — <full.package.name>` heading.
- **Idea:** the general intent of the pattern (1–2 lines).
- **Here:** how *this* code wires it up (name the concrete classes/interfaces).
- A key insight or "why it beats the naive approach" line when relevant.
- **Run:** the exact command, e.g.
  `.\mvnw.cmd -q compile exec:java "-Dexec.mainClass=<full.package.name>.main"`

Also:

- Keep the **Project structure** tree in `README.md` accurate (add the new
  pattern's folder).
- If a broadly reusable lesson came up (packages/imports, abstract vs interface,
  build/run gotchas), add a short bullet under **## Key learnings & gotchas**.

## Style

- Match the existing README tone and formatting; keep entries concise.
- Do this automatically as part of implementing/fixing the pattern — don't wait
  to be asked.
